The paper discusses security mechanisms for wireless systems, which is a common topic in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The use of Physical Layer Security (PHYSEC) and Gaussian Mixture Model (GMM) are also mentioned, which are relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The focus on wireless communication and cyber attacks suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. Finally, the mention of closed loop control and mission critical applications suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
